                            <comment id="98689" author="cstrobl" created="Mon, 10 Feb 2014 04:27:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please revise.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="98774" author="thomasd" created="Tue, 11 Feb 2014 01:30:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="98775" author="thomasd" created="Tue, 11 Feb 2014 01:31:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good to me, we could merge this into master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="99035" author="poornasubhash" created="Tue, 18 Feb 2014 23:09:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have just updated to 1.3.4 version and my existing code is breaking due to this fix. Prior to this, I have written in my code to have version increment in my client code and included $set as part of update operation. {$set:&lt;/p&gt;
{&quot;version&quot;:1}

&lt;p&gt;Two issues.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) The method  dbObjectContainsVersionProperty(**&lt;b&gt;) checks dbObject.containsField(&lt;/b&gt;*) checks only at one level of the map i.e., it try to match against $inc, but not traverse further to see if &quot;version&quot; attribute is there and adding $inc on version. Now that my update operation has both $set and $inc on version field, mongodb update fails. Hence, the issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) Also, I think increaseVersionForUpdateIfNecessary operation should be done as part of findAndModify() also.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I could fix my code to remove explicit $set, but there are places I am doing samething in findAndModify (basically I have an AOP to take care of findAndModify, updateFirst to set the vesion number). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have just created JIRA account to put these comments. Let me know if this is not the correct place for this feedback.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="99042" author="olivergierke" created="Wed, 19 Feb 2014 04:04:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The idea behind &lt;tt&gt;@Version&lt;/tt&gt; is that you explicitly don&apos;t deal with setting the value manually. The reason the change made it into the bugfix release was that the logic was broken before. So I either recommend to not manually tweak the field in your update-clause or simply remove &lt;tt&gt;@Version&lt;/tt&gt; from the field and manually handle the field everywhere.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="99043" author="poornasubhash" created="Wed, 19 Feb 2014 04:16:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree with you completely on the idea of @Version field. The reason I had manually done, is the version increment was not there earlier for update* methods(may be bug as you said).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following points are still valid.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. dbObjectContainsVersionProperty(**) is redundant and will always return false, even if the version property is present in update clause. Because the field even if present will always be nested in $inc, $set clauses.&lt;br/&gt;
2. The version increment should also happen during findAndModify. (a feature request, if not bug).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Until then, I have updated my code to depend on MongoTemplate for version increment and on my own code for findAndModify.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
